OL,3,CSoldier attack: Were there missed
OL,4,Copportunities to stop Anthony Esan?
OL,6,FBut this leaves the Teeton family with
OL,7,Fone haunting question: Why wasn't Esan
OL,8,Fthere before?
OL,10,FDuring his sentencing, Mr Justice
OL,11,FPicken said: "The psychotic disorder
OL,12,Fis part of the context for the attack
OL,13,Fbut it is not the entire context,
OL,14,Fsince the context also includes the
OL,15,Ffact that you targeted Mr Teeton, and
OL,16,Fthat you did so having carried out
OL,17,Fsearches in relation to other knife
OL,18,Fattacks, including most notably the
OL,19,Fkilling of Lee Rigby, another soldier."
