OL,3,CSoldier attack: Were there missed
OL,4,Copportunities to stop Anthony Esan?
OL,6,FThe judge said the grudge that Esan
OL,7,Fheld towards the Army worked in
OL,8,Ftandem, or in combination, with his
OL,9,Fpsychosis.
OL,11,FMr Justice Picken told Esan he
OL,12,Fpresents a "significant risk" to the
OL,13,Fpublic, adding: "You are unlikely ever
OL,14,Fto be released back into the community
OL,15,Fwhere there is a risk of recurrence."
OL,17,FEsan, of Mooring Road, Rochester, was
OL,18,Fdue to stand trial for the attack and
OL,19,Fpossession of two bladed weapons this
OL,20,Fmonth, but instead pleaded guilty to
OL,21,Fthe crimes in January.
